{"cursor":"5484","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Marital conversion' is religious conversion upon marriage, either as a\nconciliatory act, or a mandated requirement according to a particular religious\nbelief. Endogamous religious cultures may have certain opposition to interfaith\nmarriage and ethnic assimilation, and may assert prohibitions against the\nconversion (\"marrying out\") of one their own claimed adherents. Conversely, they\nmay require the marital conversion of those who wish to marry one of their\nadherents.\n","linknr":139,"url":"Marital_conversion","recorded":1362684540,"links":13,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["Marriage and religion","Religious conversion"],"headings":["Islam","Judaism","Catholicism","Sikhism","Hinduism","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[],"members":[],"related":["Religious_conversion","Marriage","Endogamy","Interfaith_marriage","Ethnic_assimilation","Apostasy","About.com","People_of_the_Book","Haraam","Apostasy","Sharia","Death_penalty","Toleration","Who_is_a_Jew?","Apostasy_in_Judaism","Jewish_assimilation","Goy","Idolatry","God","God_in_Judaism","Silent_Holocaust","United_States","Cultural_assimilation","Religious_assimilation","Roman_Catholic_Church","The_Episcopal_Church","Lutheran","Eastern_Orthodox","Unitarianism","Mormon"]}